    "description": "If you're a passionate Property Consultant with drive and ambition, Amrapali Group Holdings Services in Tiruchirappalli is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Amrapali Group Holdings Services:\nAmrapali Group Holdings Services is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Liaise with banks and NBFCs for home loan assistance to customers\n• Conduct market research and provide competitive analysis\n• Source and close property deals with prospective buyers and investors\n• Provide advisory services on property investment and market trends\n• Coordinate with architects, contractors, and project teams\n• Build relationships with channel partners and brokers\n• Manage RERA documentation and compliance requirements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Chartered Accountant (ICAI)\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Property Valuation\n• Proficiency in Market Research\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Real Estate Law\n• Proficiency in Sales Techniques\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Negotiation Skills\n• Proficiency in Investment Analysis\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Tiruchirappalli, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Amrapali Group Holdings Services!",
